overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to the provided specification
  and SOW. The assistant conducted a thorough analysis, identifying key areas
  for improvement such as missing severity scales, specific sleep disorder
  detection (COMISA, Insufficient Sleep Syndrome), weighted scoring for daytime
  sleepiness, and expanded data export capabilities. The assistant then
  systematically implemented all identified enhancements. This involved
  modifying existing types, validation schemas, UI components, and report
  generation logic to incorporate new questions, scoring mechanisms, and
  detailed narrative feedback. The outcome is a more robust and feature-complete
  sleep questionnaire application that aligns closely with the user's detailed
  requirements.
